h3. Problem Definition
When creating a clone of a ticket in a sprint, the current sprint is effected as well as the burndown chart. This is due to scope change. There is currently no warning or notification present when creating a clone notifying the user that there will be scope change and both the board and burndown report will be affected.

h3. Suggested Solution
Add in notification when cloning a ticket to know that cloning the ticket will impact both the Sprint and the Burndown report. Silmar to the warning displayed when starting a sprint as noted here: * https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=391087255
{quote}
If you do not have an estimation statistic applied to an issue, you will receive a warning when starting the sprint". Something similar when created a clone would be very helpful for the end user.
{quote}

