h3. Problem Definition
After JIRA introduced the new navigation in JIRA 6.4, users are presented with pop-up tips introducing the new features of JIRA.  I would like to turn these tool-tips off at a global level, as currently each user must dismiss the messages to turn them off. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Create a dark feature, or system option to turn them off.
 
h3. Workaround

{panel} (!) Always back up your database before performing any modification to the database. If possible, try your modifications on a test server.{panel}
The following queries can be run on the database to turn off tips for each individual user:
  
{code}INSERT INTO propertyentry VALUES (
    (SELECT max(id)+1 FROM propertyentry),
    'ApplicationUser',
    (SELECT id FROM app_user WHERE lower_user_name = '<username>'),
    'jira.user.suppressedTips.sidebar-chaperone-general-overview-tip',
    1
);{code}

{code}INSERT INTO propertyentry VALUES (
    (SELECT max(id)+1 FROM propertyentry),
    'ApplicationUser',
    (SELECT id FROM app_user WHERE lower_user_name = '<username>'),
    'jira.user.suppressedTips.sidebar-chaperone-collapse-tip',
    1
);{code}

{code}INSERT INTO propertyentry VALUES (
    (SELECT max(id)+1 FROM propertyentry),
    'ApplicationUser',
    (SELECT id FROM app_user WHERE lower_user_name = '<username>'),
    'jira.user.suppressedTips.sidebar-chaperone-disable-tip',
    1
);{code}
{code}
INSERT INTO propertyentry VALUES (
    (SELECT max(id)+1 FROM propertyentry),
    'ApplicationUser',
    (SELECT id FROM app_user WHERE lower_user_name = '<username>'),
    'jira.user.suppressedTips.split-view-intro',
    1
);{code}

